style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">37</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sADEFC67A06AE143EB0AD50BB166A9871"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;" href="#s7A2A9F6B2B4F085A53F150BB1159A7D4"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Table of Contents</font></a></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;padding-top:6px;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">APPENDIX</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;padding-top:6px;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">SEVENTH RESTATED 2002 INCENTIVE PLAN </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">OF </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:center;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">COSTCO WHOLESALE CORPORATION </font></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:24px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">1.</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Purpose of this Plan</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;text-align:justify;text-indent:48px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">The purpose of this Seventh Restated 2002 Incentive Plan of Costco Wholesale Corporation is to provide a means by which eligible recipients of Stock Awards may be given an opportunity to benefit from increases in value of the Common Stock through the granting of Options and Stock Units and to provide additional incentives through the granting of Cash-Based Awards. This Plan, which became effective on January 30, 2002 and has been amended and restated from time to time, is hereby amended, restated and renamed the Seventh Restated 2002 Incentive Plan of Costco Wholesale Corporation effective on January 30, 2015. </font></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:24px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">2.</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Definitions and Rules of Interpretation</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">2.1</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;Definitions</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">. This Plan uses the following defined terms: </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(a)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Administrator</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means the Board, the Committee, or any officer or employee of the Company to whom the Board or the Committee delegates authority to administer this Plan. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(b)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Affiliate</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means, in the case of Incentive Stock Options, a &#8220;parent&#8221; or &#8220;subsidiary&#8221; (as each is defined in Section 424 of the Code) of the Company and in the case of Awards other than Incentive Stock Options, all persons with whom the Company would be considered a single employer under Section 414(b) or Section 414(c) of the Code, except that, for purposes of determining whether there is a controlled group or common control, the language &#8220;at least 50 percent&#8221; is used instead of &#8220;at least 80 percent.&#8221; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(c)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Applicable Law&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means the legal requirements relating to the administration of equity compensation plans, including under applicable U.S. state corporate laws, U.S. federal and applicable state securities laws, other U.S. federal and state laws, the Code, any stock exchange rules or regulations and the applicable laws, rules and regulations of any other country or jurisdiction where Awards are granted under this Plan, as such laws, rules, regulations and requirements shall be in place from time to time. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(d)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Award&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means a grant of an Option, an award of a Stock Unit or a grant of a Cash-Based Award in accordance with the terms of this Plan.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(e)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Award Agreement&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means a written agreement between the Company and a holder of an Award evidencing the terms and conditions of an individual Award. Each Award Agreement shall be subject to the terms and conditions of this Plan.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(f)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Award Shares&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means Shares issuable under an Award. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(g)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Board</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#8221; means the board of directors of the Company. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(h)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Cash-Based Award&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means an Award denominated in a dollar amount granted under Section 10.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(i)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Change of Control&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;is defined in Section 12.4. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(j)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Code&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means the Internal Revenue Code of 1986. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(k)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Committee&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means a committee composed of Company Directors appointed in accordance with the Company&#8217;s Articles of Incorporation and Bylaws and Section 4. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">38</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sADEFC67A06AE143EB0AD50BB166A9871"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;" href="#s7A2A9F6B2B4F085A53F150BB1159A7D4"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Table of Contents</font></a></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(l)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Company&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means Costco Wholesale Corporation, a Washington corporation.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#160;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(m)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Company Director&#8221; </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">means a member of the Board. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(n)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Consultant&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means an individual who, or an employee of any entity that, provides bona fide services to the Company or an Affiliate not in connection with the offer or sale of securities in a capital-raising transaction, but who is not an Employee. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(o)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Continuous Service&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means that the Participant&#8217;s service with the Company or an Affiliate, whether as an Employee, Director or Consultant, is not interrupted or terminated by a Termination as defined in Section&#160;2.1(ss). </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(p)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Covered Employee&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;has the meaning as determined for purposes of Section 162(m) of the Code. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(q)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Disability&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means the permanent and total disability of a person within the meaning of Section 22(e)(3) of the Code. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(r)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Director&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means a member of the board of directors of the Company or an Affiliate. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(s)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Divestiture&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means any transaction or event that the Board specifies as a Divestiture under Section&#160;12.5. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(t)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Employee&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means a regular employee of the Company or an Affiliate, including an officer or Director, who is treated as an employee in the personnel records of the Company or an Affiliate, but not individuals who are classified by the Company or an Affiliate as: (i) leased from or otherwise employed by a third party, (ii) independent contractors, or (iii) intermittent or temporary workers. The Company&#8217;s or an Affiliate&#8217;s classification of an individual as an &#8220;Employee&#8221; (or as not an &#8220;Employee&#8221;) for purposes of this Plan shall not be altered retroactively even if that classification is changed retroactively for another purpose as a result of an audit, litigation or otherwise. A Participant shall not cease to be an Employee due to transfers between locations of the Company, or between the Company and an Affiliate, or to any successor to the Company or an Affiliate that assumes the Participant&#8217;s Award under Section 12, unless such event results in a Termination as defined in Section 2.1(ss). Neither service as a Director nor receipt of a director&#8217;s fee shall be sufficient to make a Director an &#8220;Employee.&#8221; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(u)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means the Securities Exchange Act of 1934. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(v)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Executive&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means an individual who is subject to Section 16 of the Exchange Act or who is a &#8220;Covered Employee,&#8221; in either case because of the individual&#8217;s relationship with the Company or an Affiliate. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(w)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Expiration Date&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means, with respect to an Option, the date stated in the Award Agreement as the expiration date of the Option or, if no such date is stated in the Award Agreement, then the last day of the maximum exercise period for the Option, disregarding the effect of a Participant&#8217;s Termination or any other event that would shorten that period. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(x)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Fair Market Value&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means the value of Shares as determined under Section 18.2. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(y)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Fundamental Transaction&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means any transaction or event described in Section 12.3. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(z)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Grant Date&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means the date the Administrator approves the grant of an Award. However, if the Administrator specifies that an Award&#8217;s Grant Date is a future date or the date on which a condition is satisfied, the Grant Date for such Award is that future date or the date that the condition is satisfied. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(aa)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#8220;Incentive Stock Option&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means an Option intended to qualify as an incentive stock option under Section&#160;422 of the Code and designated as an Incentive Stock Option in the Option Agreement for that Option.</font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">39</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sADEFC67A06AE143EB0AD50BB166A9871"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;" href="#s7A2A9F6B2B4F085A53F150BB1159A7D4"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Table of Contents</font></a></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">(bb)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#8220;Nonstatutory Option&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means any Option other than an Incentive Stock Option. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">(cc)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#8220;Non-Employee Director&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means a Director of the Company who either (i) is not a current Employee or Officer of the Company or its parent or a subsidiary, does not receive compensation (directly or indirectly) from the Company or its parent or a subsidiary for services rendered as a consultant or in any capacity other than as a Director (except for an amount as to which disclosure would not be required under Item 404(a) of Regulation S-K promulgated pursuant to the Securities Act (&#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Regulation S-K</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#8221;)), and does not possess an interest in any other transaction as to which disclosure would be required under Item 404(a) of Regulation S-K; or (ii) is otherwise considered a &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">non-employee director</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#8221; for purposes of Rule 16b-3. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">(dd)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#8220;Objectively Determinable Performance Condition&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;shall mean any one or more of the following performance criteria, either individually, alternatively or in any combination, applied to either the Company as a whole or to a business unit, Affiliate or business segment, either individually, alternatively or in any combination, and measured either annually or cumulatively over a period of years, on an absolute basis or relative to a pre-established target, to previous years&#8217; results or to a designated comparison group, in each case as specified by the Committee in the Award: (i) cash flow; (ii) earnings (including gross margin, earnings before interest and taxes, earnings before taxes, and net earnings); (iii) earnings per share; (iv) growth in earnings or earnings per share; (v)&#160;stock price; (vi) return on equity or average shareowners&#8217; equity; (vii) total shareowner return; (viii) return on capital; (ix) return on assets or net assets; (x) return on investment; (xi) revenue; (xii) income or net income; (xiii)&#160;operating income or net operating income; (xiv) operating profit or net operating profit; (xv) operating margin; (xvi) return on operating revenue; (xvii) market share; (xviii) sales or revenue growth; (xix) overhead or other expense reduction; (xx) growth in shareowner value relative to the moving average of the S&amp;P 500 Index or a peer group index; (xxi) credit rating; (xxii) strategic plan development and implementation; (xxiii) improvement in workforce diversity, and (xxiv) any other similar criteria. The Committee may provide that any evaluation of performance under an Objectively Determinable Performance Condition will exclude any of the following events that occurs during a performance period: (A) asset write-downs; (B) litigation or claim judgments or settlements; (C) the effect of changes in tax law, accounting principles or other such laws or provisions affecting reported results; (D) accruals for reorganization and restructuring programs; and (E) any extraordinary non-recurring items as described in Accounting Principles Board Opinion No. 30 and/or in management&#8217;s discussion and analysis of financial condition and results of operations appearing in the Company&#8217;s annual report to shareowners for the applicable year. To the extent such exclusions affect Awards that are intended to constitute Performance-Based Compensation, the exclusions shall be prescribed in a form that satisfies the requirements for Performance-Based Compensation. In addition, in the event of any stock split, reverse stock split, recapitalization, combination or reclassification of stock, stock dividend, spin-off, extraordinary cash dividend or similar change to the capital structure of the Company that impacts a performance condition appropriate and equitable adjustments to the condition shall be made.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">(ee) </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Option&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means a right to purchase Shares of the Company granted under this Plan. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(ff) </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Option Agreement&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means the document evidencing the grant of an Option. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(gg) </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Option Price&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means the price payable under an Option for Shares, not including any amount payable in respect of withholding or other taxes. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:left;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(hh) </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Outside Director&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means a Company Director who either (i) is not a current employee of the Company or an &#8220;affiliated corporation&#8221; (within the meaning of Treasury Regulations promulgated under Section 162(m) of the Code), is not a former employee of the Company or an &#8220;affiliated corporation&#8221; receiving compensation for prior services (other than benefits under a tax qualified pension plan), was not an officer of the Company or an &#8220;affiliated corporation&#8221; at any time and is not currently receiving direct or indirect remuneration from the Company or an &#8220;affiliated corporation&#8221; for services in any capacity other than as a Director or (ii) is otherwise considered an &#8220;outside director&#8221; for purposes of Section 162(m) of the Code. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(ii) </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Participant&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means a person to whom an Award is granted pursuant to this Plan or, if applicable, such other person who holds an outstanding Award. </font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">40</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sADEFC67A06AE143EB0AD50BB166A9871"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><a style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(jj) </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#8221; means &#8220;qualified performance-based compensation&#8221; within the meaning of Section 162(m) of the Code and the Treasury Regulations promulgated thereunder.</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div Costco Wholesale Corporation, as amended and restated from time to time. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font 16(b) of the Exchange Act. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div value per share, of the Company or other securities substituted for the common stock under Section 12. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font granted under this Plan, including an Option or Stock Unit. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Stock Unit&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means an award giving the right to receive Shares granted under Section 9 below. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(rr) </font><font substitution for, or upon the conversion of, an option granted by another entity to purchase equity securities in the granting entity. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(ss) </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">&#8220;Termination&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;means &#8220;termination of employment&#8221; or &#8220;separation from service&#8221; as defined in Section 409A of the Code. However, with respect to an Employee, Termination will occur at the date reasonably anticipated by the Company and Employee that a Participant&#8217;s level of service will permanently decrease to 21% or less of the average level of service provided by the Participant over the immediately preceding 36 months period (or if providing services for less than 36 months, such lesser period). If a Participant&#8217;s status changes from an Employee to an independent contractor or from an independent contractor to an Employee, whether there has been a Termination will be determined in accordance with the regulations under Section 409A of the Code. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">2.2</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;Rules of Interpretation.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;Any reference to a &#8220;Section,&#8221; without more, is to a Section of this Plan. Captions and titles are used for convenience in this Plan and shall not, by themselves, determine the meaning of this Plan. Except when otherwise indicated by the context, the singular includes the plural and vice versa. Any reference to a statute is also a reference to the applicable rules and regulations adopted under that statute. Any reference to a statute, rule or regulation, or to a section of a statute, rule or regulation, is a reference to that statute, rule, regulation, or section as amended from time to time, both before and after the effective date of this Plan and including any successor provisions. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-family:Times New Roman; Term of this Plan</font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:48px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">3.1 </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;Number of Shares. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Subject to adjustment under Section 12, the maximum number of Shares that may be granted as Awards under this Plan is 23.5 million plus any Shares previously authorized for grant under this Plan or its predecessors that have not been granted as of the date of this amendment and restatement plus any Shares covered by Awards granted under this Plan or its predecessors prior to the date of this amendment and restatement that are subsequently cancelled or expire unexercised or unvested. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">3.2  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Limitation on Award of Stock Units.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;Subject to adjustment as provided in Section 12 below, the maximum number of Shares that may be issued shall be reduced by 1.75 Shares for each Share granted in a Stock Award in which the Participant is issued Shares without tendering to the Company payment of an amount in connection therewith equal to the Fair Market Value of such Shares on the date of the Stock Award; </font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">41</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sADEFC67A06AE143EB0AD50BB166A9871"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;" href="#s7A2A9F6B2B4F085A53F150BB1159A7D4"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Table of Contents</font></a></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">provided however that, to the extent that previously-issued Shares are later forfeited under the terms and conditions of the Stock Award, then any Shares so forfeited shall not count against the limit set forth in this section 3.2. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">3.3  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Source of Shares. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Award Shares may be authorized but unissued Shares. If an Award is terminated, expires, or otherwise becomes unexercisable without having been exercised in full, the unpurchased Shares that were subject to the Award shall revert to this Plan and shall again be available for future issuance under this Plan. The following Shares shall not again be made available for issuance as Awards under this Plan: (i) Shares actually issued under this Plan in a Stock Option even if repurchased by the Company; (ii) Shares not issued or delivered as a result of the net settlement of an outstanding Option, or (iii) Shares used to pay the exercise price or withholding taxes related to an outstanding Award. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;text-indent:-24px;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Administration </font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:24px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;4.1  General </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(a)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">The Board shall have ultimate responsibility for administering this Plan. The Board may delegate certain of its responsibilities to a Committee, which shall consist of at least two members of the Board and solely of Outside Directors. The Board or the Committee may further delegate its responsibilities to any Employee of the Company or any Affiliate. Where this Plan specifies that an action is to be taken or a determination made by the Committee, only the Committee may take that action or make that determination. Where this Plan references the &#8220;Administrator,&#8221; the action may be taken or determination made by the Board, the Committee, or other Administrator. Where this Plan references the Board, the action may be taken or determination made by the Board or the Committee. However, only the Board may approve any amendment to this Plan for which shareholder approval is necessary or desirable to comply with any Applicable Law, only the Board or the Committee may approve Awards to Executives, and an Administrator other than the Board or the Committee may grant Options and Stock Units only within guidelines established by the Board or Committee. Moreover, all actions and determinations by any Administrator are subject to the provisions of this Plan. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(b)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">So long as the Company has registered an outstanding a class of equity securities under Section&#160;12 of the Exchange Act, the Committee shall consist of Company Directors who are &#8220;Non-Employee Directors&#8221; and who are &#8220;Outside Directors.&#8221; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;4.2  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Authority of Administrator.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;Subject to the other provisions of this Plan, the Administrator shall have the authority, in a manner that complies with Section 409A of the Code: </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(a)  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to make and determine the types of Awards, provided that no Non-Employee Director may be granted Awards for more than 12,000 Shares in any fiscal year (subject to adjustment under Section&#160;12); </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(b)  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to determine the Fair Market Value of Shares; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(c)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to determine the Option Price; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">42</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sADEFC67A06AE143EB0AD50BB166A9871"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;" href="#s7A2A9F6B2B4F085A53F150BB1159A7D4"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Table of Contents</font></a></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(d)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to determine Objectively Determinable Performance Conditions; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(e)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to select the Participants; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(i)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to determine the other terms of each Award, including but not limited to the time or times at which Options may be exercised, whether and under what conditions an Award is assignable, and whether an Option is a Nonstatutory Option or an Incentive Stock Option; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(j)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to modify or amend any Award, including, without limitation, to extend the period during which an Option may be exercised, but neither the Administrator, the Board, nor the Committee shall have the authority to reduce the Option Price of any outstanding Option without obtaining the approval of the Company&#8217;s shareholders or to make a modification or amendment under this Section 4.2(j) that results in an Award that was exempt from Section 409A of the Code becoming subject to Section 409A and noncompliant with Section&#160;409A or an Award that is subject to Section 409A of the Code becoming noncompliant with Section 409A;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(k)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to authorize any person to sign any Award Agreement or other document related to this Plan on behalf of the Company; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(l)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to determine the form of any Award Agreement or other document related to this Plan, and whether that document, including signatures, may be in electronic form; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(m)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to interpret this Plan and any Award Agreement or document related to this Plan; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(n)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to correct any defect, remedy any omission, or reconcile any inconsistency in this Plan, any Award Agreement or any other document related to this Plan; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(o)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to adopt, amend, and revoke rules and regulations under this Plan, including rules and regulations relating to sub-plans and Plan addenda; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(p)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;to adopt, amend, and revoke rules and procedures relating to the operation and administration of this Plan to accommodate non-U.S. Participants and the requirements of Applicable Law such as: (i) rules and procedures regarding the conversion of local currency, withholding procedures and the handling of stock certificates to comply with local practice and requirements, and (ii) sub-plans and Plan addenda for non-U.S. Participants; and </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(q)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">to make all other determinations the Administrator deems necessary or advisable for the administration of this Plan. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;4.3  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Scope of Discretion</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">. Subject to the last sentence of this Section 4.3, on all matters for which this Plan confers the authority, right or power on the Board, the Committee, or other Administrator to make decisions, that body may make those decisions in its sole and absolute discretion. Moreover, but again subject to the last sentence of this Section 4.3, in making those decisions the Board, Committee or other Administrator need not treat all persons eligible to receive Awards, all Participants, all Awards or all Award Shares the same way. However, the discretion of the Board, Committee or other Administrator is subject to the specific provisions and specific limitations of this Plan, as well as all rights conferred on specific Participants by Award Agreements and other agreements. </font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">43</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sADEFC67A06AE143EB0AD50BB166A9871"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><a style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:24px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div Consultants, including to prospective Employees, Directors and Consultants conditioned on the beginning of their service for the Company or an Affiliate. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;5.2  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Section 162(m) Limitation.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(a)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">So long as the Company is a &#8220;publicly held corporation&#8221; within the meaning of Section 162(m) of the Code: (i) the maximum number of each type of Stock Award intended to constitute Performance-Based Compensation granted to any Employee or prospective Employee within any fiscal year of the Company shall not exceed 500,000 Shares for each type of award, subject to adjustment under Section 12, (ii) the maximum amount of Cash-Based Awards intended to constitute Performance-Based Compensation granted to any Employee or prospective Employee within any fiscal year of the Company shall not exceed $3 million, and (iii) Awards may be granted to an Executive only by the Committee (and, notwithstanding Section 4.1(a), not by the Board). </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(b)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Notwithstanding any other provision of this Plan to the contrary, the Committee shall have the discretion to determine whether an Award will be structured in a manner intended to qualify as Performance-Based Compensation. Any Stock Unit or Cash-Based Award that is intended qualify as Performance-Based Compensation must vest or become exercisable contingent on the achievement of one or more Objectively Determinable Performance Conditions. Prior to the payment of any compensation under an Award intended to qualify as Performance-Based Compensation, the Committee shall certify the extent to which any Objectively Determinable Performance Conditions and any other material terms under such Award have been satisfied (other than in cases where such relate solely to the increase in the value of the Common Stock). </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(c)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Notwithstanding satisfaction of any completion of any Objectively Determinable Performance Condition, to the extent specified at the time of grant of an Award to Covered Employees, the number or amount of Shares, Options, Cash-Based Awards or other benefits granted, issued, retainable and/or vested under an Award on account of satisfaction of such Objectively Determinable Performance Conditions may be reduced by the Committee on the basis of such further considerations as the Committee in its sole discretion shall determine; provided that such reduction is structured in a manner intended to satisfy the requirements for Performance-Based Compensation under Section 162(m) of the Code. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt;"><tr><td style="width:24px;"></td><td></td></tr><tr><td style="vertical-align:top"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;padding-left:0px;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">6.</font></div></td><td style="vertical-align:top;"><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Terms and Conditions of Options </font></div></td></tr></table><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;padding-left:24px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-bottom:16px;padding-top:6px;text-align:justify;text-indent:32px;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">The following rules apply to all Options: </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">6.1</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">&#32;&#32;Price.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;No Option may have an Option Price less than 100% of the Fair Market Value of the Shares on the Grant Date. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;6.2  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Term.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;No Option shall be exercisable after its Expiration Date. No Option may have an Expiration Date that is more than ten years after its Grant Date. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;6.3  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Vesting.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;</font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(a)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Options shall be exercisable in accordance with a schedule related to the Grant Date, the date the Participant&#8217;s directorship, employment or consultancy begins, or a different date specified in the Option Agreement evidencing such Option; provided that no Option shall be exercisable until one year from the Grant Date except as provided below. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;padding-right:24px;">(b)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">For Options granted after October 10, 2003, the Administrator shall have the authority in its discretion to permit the exercise of an Option prior to the expiration of one year from the Grant Date based on the Pro </font></div><br><div style="text-align:center;"><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">44</font></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><a name="sADEFC67A06AE143EB0AD50BB166A9871"></a><div><div style="line-height:120%;font-size:10pt;"><a style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;" href="#s7A2A9F6B2B4F085A53F150BB1159A7D4"><font style="font-family:inherit;font-size:10pt;">Table of Contents</font></a></div></div><br><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Rata Number of Shares formula in Section 8.4(a) hereof and in an amount not to exceed 20% of the Option Shares granted on that Grant Date. In the event that the Participant, whether voluntarily or involuntarily, experiences a change to an employment status or position in the Company that is not eligible for Option grants or is eligible for a lesser number of Options, except as otherwise determined by the Administrator the Option Shares shall cease to vest at the time of such change, except that the Participant shall be entitled to a vesting of a Pro Rata Number of Shares computed in accordance with Section 8.4(a) using the next anniversary of the Grant Date following the change in status. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Grants to Non-Employee Directors shall be vested and exercisable at the Grant Date. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;6.4  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-weight:bold;">Form of Payment. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(a)  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">The Administrator shall determine the acceptable form and method of payment for exercising an Option. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(b)  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Acceptable forms of payment for all Option Shares are cash, check or wire transfer, denominated in U.S. dollars except as specified by the Administrator for non-U.S. Employees or non-U.S. sub-plans. </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;(c)  </font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">In addition, the Administrator may permit payment to be made by any of the following methods: </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;padding-right:24px;">(i)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">other Shares, or the designation of other Shares, which have a Fair Market Value on the date of surrender equal to the Option Price of the Shares as to which the Option is being exercised; </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><br></font></div><div style="line-height:120%;padding-left:0px;text-align:justify;text-indent:24px;"><font style="text-align:justify;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;padding-right:24px;">(ii)</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">provided that a public market exists for the Shares, through a &#8220;same day sale&#8221; commitment from the Participant and a broker-dealer that is a member of the National Association of Securities Dealers (an &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">NASD Dealer</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#8221;) under which the Participant irrevocably elects to exercise the Option and the NASD Dealer irrevocably commits to forward an amount equal to the Option Price, directly to the Company, upon receipt of the Option Shares (a &#8220;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;">Cashless Exercise</font><font style="font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&#8221;); </font></div><div style="line-height:120%;text-align:justify;font-size:10pt;"><font
